		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>From what I have read hitting is based on the following factor in order of importance:<br><br>1) Level between you and the mob, i.e. the higher lvl you are vs the mob you are fighting the more hits you will get and visa versa<br><br>2) Your Attack factor.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since strength raises your attack factor, strength has some importance too.<br><br>3) Dex affects your to hit possibility, but not as much as the above two.<br><br>Having leveled 3 melee characters with the highest being 51 it seems numbers 1 and 2 matter a great deal more than item 3.  I switched from a balance of Str and Dex gear to mostly str gear and it appears I hit a lot more often then before.<br><br>All of this is from personal observation and not actually calculating the hit and miss ratios, so I may be wrong.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Boric Blackrune<br>The Free Company<br>Erolissi Marr Server<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
